article.headline: UAB 77, Old Dominion 62
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Channing Toney scored 28 points to help UAB beat Old Dominion 77-62 on Saturday. Toney made 8 of 13 from 3-point range for the Blazers (4-0), who shot 11 of 22 from beyond the arc and 51 percent from the floor (26 of 51). Old Dominion (1-1) connected on just 20 of 66 of its field goals. Lawrence Kinnard added 17 points for UAB. Paul Delaney, who went 8-for-8 from the free-throw line, scored 15 points. Marsharee Neely led Old Dominion with 14 points, while Gerald Lee added 10.
